## I7. Add runtime validation to JSON.parse in ws-client

**File 1:** `src/lib/ws-client.ts` around line 216

```ts
msg = JSON.parse(raw) as RpcMessage;
```

**Fix:** Add a minimal runtime shape check before the cast:
```ts
const parsed = JSON.parse(raw);
if (typeof parsed !== 'object' || parsed === null || parsed.jsonrpc !== '2.0') {
  console.warn('[ws-client] Invalid JSON-RPC message received', parsed);
  return;
}
msg = parsed as RpcMessage;
```
Adjust to fit the existing control flow. Don't break on malformed messages — log and skip.

